        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:448:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/385/480",
        "text": [
          "۳۸۵. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): مِنْ هَوَانِ الدُّنْيَا عَلَى اللهِ أَنَّهُ لَا يُعْصَى إِلَّا فِيهَا، وَلَا يُنَالُ مَا عِنْدَهُ إِلَّا بِتَرْكِهَا."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "385. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: It is (the proof of the) humbleness of the world before Allāh that He is disobeyed only herein and His favours cannot be achieved except by abandoning it."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
